OL,6,FShell has sparked fresh calls for a
OL,7,Ftougher windfall tax, after it revealed
OL,8,Fthat its former boss's pay package rose
OL,9,Fby more than 50 per cent to #9.7m last
OL,10,Fyear.
OL,12,FBen van Beurden's pay jumped 53 per
OL,13,Fcent from #6.3m in 2021. The 2022
OL,14,Ffigure includes a #2.6m annual bonus
OL,15,Fand a #4.9m long-term shares award on
OL,16,Ftop of his #1.4m annual salary.
OL,18,FThe bonus followed Shell's record $40bn
OL,19,F(#33.5bn) profits last year as energy
OL,20,Fprices surged.
